[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `apply_collection_strategy`. In production, this runs as a Lambda function triggered by EventBridge after the nightly scoring completes. It reads predictions from DynamoDB and routes each balance to the appropriate collection queue. Here we show the routing logic as a standalone function.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def apply_collection_strategy(predictions: list[dict]) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Route scored balances to collection strategy queues based on propensity.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the strategy engine. It takes model predictions and turns them
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     into operational decisions. The thresholds are business parameters:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     adjust them based on your staff capacity, payment plan costs, and
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     financial assistance policies.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, this function runs in Lambda and writes routing decisions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     to an SQS queue or directly updates the collection workflow system.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         predictions: List of prediction dicts from DynamoDB, each containing
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                      balance_id, propensity_score, balance_amount, etc.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Summary dict with counts per strategy queue.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     routing_summary = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "standard_statements": 0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "payment_plan_offer": 0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "financial_counselor_outreach": 0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "financial_assistance_screening": 0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for pred in predictions:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         score = float(pred["propensity_score"])
