[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's the full pipeline assembled into a single function. This is what your orchestration (EventBridge + Step Functions, or a simple script) would call.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def run_propensity_pipeline():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run the full propensity-to-pay pipeline end-to-end.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, Steps 1-2 are a Glue job (pulling from real billing data).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Step 3 runs monthly (retraining). Steps 4-6 run nightly (scoring and routing).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Here we run everything sequentially for demonstration.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 1: Generate synthetic data (in production: Glue ETL from billing system).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("=" * 60)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Step 1: Generating synthetic balance data")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("=" * 60)
